[{"id":"VR857496","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a scatterplot in the first quadrant of a coordinate plane. The horizontal axis is labeled “Sine of theta sub 2.,” and the numbers 0.0 through 1.0, in increments of 0.2, are indicated. The vertical axis is labeled “Sine of theta sub 1” and the numbers 0.0 through 1.0, in increments of 0.2, are indicated. There are 10 data points in the scatterplot at the approximate locations. Data point 1, 0.05 comma 0.05. Data point 2, 0.2 comma 0.15. Data point 3, 0.35 comma 0.3. Data point 4, 0.425 comma 0.325. Data point 5, 0.5 comma 0.39. Data point 6, 0.65 comma 0.52. Data point 7, 0.82 comma 0.61. Data point 8, 0.88 comma 0.69. Data point 9, 0.95 comma 0.77. Data point 10, 0.99 comma 0.79.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR857496.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">In an optics experiment, a beam of light travels across an interface between two transparent materials, Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>. Measurements are made of the following two quantities for a range of values.</p><ul class=\"unordered_list style:1\"><li class=\"list_item\"><p class=\"list_paragraph\">The angle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 1\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> between the normal to the interface and the beam in Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span></p></li><li class=\"list_item\"><p class=\"list_paragraph\">The angle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 2\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> between the normal to the interface and the beam in Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span></p></li></ul><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">As shown in the graph, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the sine of theta sub 1\"><math alttext=\"the sine of theta sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>sin</mi><mo>⁡</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> is then plotted as a function of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the sine of theta sub 2\"><math alttext=\"the sine of theta sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>sin</mi><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>. Which of the following statements is consistent with the graph?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR857496_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Light has the same speed in both materials.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The refractive index is greater for Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> than for Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The beam angles <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 1\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 2\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> are directly proportional to one another.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Total internal reflection is possible when light travels in Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> toward Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>.</p>"],"answer":1}]